content: The contrast on the diff popup in dark mode is a little too much. Make the green and red colors a little more subtle in dark mode.
Even more subtle. See how GitHub looks. Also, can you add code formatting into the popup?

In the title of the popup, can you remove the project directory from the path? project directory is the value after "Project Directory:" in the page header. 

So "File Diff: /Users/dgish/code-git/superhero-ai/superhero-python/example_project/GenAI_creativity_scripts/readme.md" would become "File Diff: GenAI_creativity_scripts/readme.md"
Does that variable need to get passed in?
Didn't work. Use the same variable that the page header uses.
